[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    467[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Heads-up at the top names every major production gap before the code starts (no real PBM ingestion, no NCPDP X12 parsing, no validated PDC methodology against PQA specifications, no randomized-pilot infrastructure, no production propensity-score modeling, no LP-based heterogeneous allocator, no live PCP-EHR integration, no real outcome-evaluation methodology with pre-registration).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    468[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The PHI-logging guidance at the module level: [38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173m"Never log a raw (patient_id, therapeutic_class, barrier) join along with clinical context; the row implicitly identifies both the medication and the suspected reason. The barrier-classifications table and the recommendation log are highly inferential PHI."[38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;191;97;106m The right framing for an inference-rich domain.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    469[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The barrier-classifier framing: [38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173m"The barrier classifier is the part most plans skip and the part that distinguishes a good adherence program from a reminder spam campaign."[38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;191;97;106m Sets the right operational expectation up front.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    470[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The settled-lag rationale: [38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173m"30-day settled lag: retail claims arrive on a 1-2 day lag, mail-order on a 5-14 day lag, and specialty up to 30. Computing PDC against claims that haven't all arrived yet produces noisy, biased numbers that systematically under-estimate adherence for mail-order users."[38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;191;97;106m Saves a reader from a real production bug.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    471[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The carry-forward PDC math: [38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173m"Each fill contributes a half-open interval [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m[fill_date, fill_date + days_supply)[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;180;142;173m. Overlapping fills (early refills, stockpiling) extend the covered set without double-counting. The set membership test for 'is day d covered' is what makes mail-order, retail, and synchronized refills all produce the same PDC for the same actual adherence."[38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;191;97;106m Captures the entire PDC-correctness intuition.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    472[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The barrier-fit dot product: [38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173m"Patient barriers [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m[cost: 0.72, beliefs: 0.21][38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;180;142;173m dotted with cost-assistance supports [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m{cost: 1.0, beliefs: 0.0, ...}[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;180;142;173m = 0.72. Same patient with text-reminder supports [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m{forgetfulness: 1.0, cost: 0.0, ...}[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;180;142;173m = 0.0."[38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;191;97;106m Concrete arithmetic example beats abstract description.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    473[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The cost-efficiency framing in the priority math: [38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173m"The cost_efficiency weight is what stops a $80 pharmacist consult from being chosen over a $0.05 reminder for every candidate where uplift is similar."[38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;191;97;106m Names the failure mode the term prevents.[K
